The paper deals with clock synchronization in dynamic networks, which involves distributed algorithms and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves network communication and synchronization, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper uses algorithms and analysis to achieve optimal synchronization, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
